  "prompt": "What does it mean when you have blood clots but no period?",
  "response": "Blood clots without a period can indicate several potential health conditions:\n\n1. Possible medical reasons:\n- Hormonal imbalances\n- Pregnancy complications\n- Ectopic pregnancy\n- Miscarriage\n- Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)\n- Uterine fibroids\n- Endometriosis\n\n2. Potential symptoms that may accompany blood clots:\n- Abdominal pain\n- Cramping\n- Irregular bleeding\n- Unusual discharge\n\n3. Important considerations:\n- Blood clots larger than a quarter\n- Persistent or recurring clots\n- Accompanied by severe pain\n- Unexplained weight loss\n- Fever\n\n4. Recommended actions:\n- Consult a healthcare professional\n- Get a gynecological examination\n- Consider pregnancy test\n- Discuss potential underlying conditions\n- Undergo necessary diagnostic tests\n\n5. Healthcare provider might:\n- Perform ultrasound\n- Check hormone levels\n- Review medical history\n- Conduct blood tests\n\nThis information is general guidance. Individual situations vary, so professional medical advice is crucial for accurate diagnosis and treatment.",
